tip.text: Fabulous food and top notch service. Say yes to the sambal selection, beautifully fresh Gohu Ikan Tuna, melt-in-your-mouth Babi Guling, and save room for the Klappertaart. Can't wait to return!
Awesome little spot for a quiet mani/pedi.  Am a big fan of Carol's handpainted nail art: $480 + $30/finger for a soft gel manicure.

venue.name: The Loft by The Nail Library

tip.text: Fabulous cocktails and fresh seafood-focused, modern cuisine. Ask for a table up front to truly appreciate the beauty of the padi field. Snuggle on the daybed in the middle of the field afterward!
Every meal I've ever had here is a revelation in texture and flavor. Inventive, affordable modern French cuisine incorporating local ingredients. The cote de boeuf is a delicious, must-have addition!

tip.text: This dai pai dong is in the alley behind 18 King St. Decent scrambled eggs & charsiew on rice, although too over-cooked for my liking. Lok Heung Yuen in Central still tops  in my book.
Cheap, highly addictive 滑蛋叉燒飯 (scrambled eggs & charsiew on rice). They're also known for the version with shrimp. Pour their special soy over for extra flavor! Go at noon to avoid lunchtime queues.

tip.text: Excellent claypot rice cooked over charcoal. Try the white eel and pork. Also delicious fried tofu!

tip.text: Get the half tendon half beef noodles (半筋半肉), and chuck in some of their homemade chili paste to add spice and umami flavors to an already delicious herbal broth. Deeeelish!
